===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}}, West Germanic ''*barthaz'' (cognate with Middle Dutch ''[[baert]]'', German {{term|Bart|lang=de}}, Old Norse ''[[barðr]]'' etc.).

Ultimate origin probably Proto-Indo-European *bʰardʰ-eh₂, with other derivations including Latin {{l|la|barba}}, Russian {{term|sc=Cyrl|борода|tr=boroda|lang=ru}}, Lithuanian {{l|lt|barzda}} etc.

